Program: Great Lives
Title: Anthony Horowitz chooses the life of Alfred Hitchcock
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b075pz7z
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 8 Apr 2016
Anthony Horowitz regards Alfred Hitchcock as a genius who changed the language of cinema and made some of the most memorable films of the twentieth century. However, the film director is also seen as a troubled man who was at times abusive towards some of his leading ladies. The expert witness is Nathalie Morris; Senior Curator at the BFI, National Archive. The presenter is Matthew Parris and the producer is Perminder Khatkar. Show less